A political battle is shaping up in the Keiyo South parliamentary race after athlete Wilson Kipsang officially declared his interest in the seat.Kipsang spoke to residents on Saturday night at a homecoming party to celebrate his win at the Tokyo Marathon. He said he is ready to capture the seat currently held by Jackson Kiptanui, who has set his eyes on the Elgeyo Marakwet governor race.The marathon champion was received by family and hundreds of supporters at the Eldoret Airport (pictured). Kipsang made 10 stopovers to greet supporters who stopped him and demanded that he speaks to them. &ldquo;My next marathon is the race to Parliament. I thank you all for your prayers and I hope you will continue praying for me,&rdquo; a jubilant Kipsang told supporters at Kocholwa trading centre.